# Project foundation

Before substantial work:

1. Read `memory/agreements.md`.
2. Read `memory/now.md` when it exists.
3. Read `memory/intent.md` when product intent or scope matters.
4. Inspect repository and Git state before assumptions or changes.

Follow Git identity and authority rules in `memory/agreements.md`. Use the configured privacy-safe Git identity. Inspect commit metadata before pushing. Do not expose identity values in repository content. Do not commit, push or perform destructive Git operations unless explicitly authorised.

Do not expose personal or local-system information, secrets or private configuration. Do not add AI authorship or co-author metadata to commits.

When `memory/now.md` points to a `specialist/` file, read that file for the active task. Pointers do not automatically mean every specialist file belongs in default context.

Keep changes focused, verified and proportionate. Do not duplicate full agreements here — they live in `memory/agreements.md`.
